# Auth & Retreat Update Plan

## Goal
1.  Display the Retreat page description in multiple lines.
2.  Implement a simple Login system to protect the Admin page.

## Proposed Changes

### [RetreatPage.jsx]
-   **Text Styling**: Remove `whitespace-nowrap overflow-hidden text-ellipsis`. Add `whitespace-pre-line` to respect newlines.

### [Auth & DataContext]
-   **State**: Add `isAuthenticated` and `login(password)` / `logout()` methods to `DataContext`.
-   **Persistence**: Save auth state to `localStorage` (or `sessionStorage` for security, but user wants convenience).
-   **Password**: Hardcode a simple password (e.g., "sandol1234") in the client for now (MVP).

### [LoginPage.jsx] (New)
-   Simple form with Password input.
-   On success: [setAllData](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/context/DataContext.jsx#37-41) (if needed) or just `login()`, then redirect to `/admin`.

### [Header.jsx]
-   Add a "Login" button (if not logged in) or "Admin" / "Logout" button (if logged in).
-   Position: "Next to the top image" - implies Header right side.

### [App.jsx]
-   Add Route for `/login`.
-   Protect `/admin`: Wrap [AdminPage](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#141-238) in a `ProtectedRoute` component or check auth inside [AdminPage](file:///c:/Users/admin/.gemini/%EC%82%B0%EB%8F%8C%EA%B5%90%ED%9A%8C%20%ED%99%88%ED%8E%98%EC%9D%B4%EC%A7%80/src/pages/AdminPage.jsx#141-238).

## Verification Plan
1.  Check Retreat page text wrapping.
2.  Verify Login button appears in Header.
3.  Verify clicking Login goes to Login page.
4.  Verify correct password grants access to Admin.
5.  Verify direct access to `/admin` redirects to Login (optional, but good practice).
